<br>
It is never funny when someone decides to take his or her own life, however, the idea of casting blame on something like Everquest is ridiculous in its conception.  It also seemed that the reporter was belittling the players (addicts) of EQ when she walked out dressed in a robe.  Possibly trying to give the impression that Everquest is meant for kids and the immature.  Just the feeling I got through watching the interview(s), so on.   If you noticed she seemed to carry on a more ‘mature’ conversation with Ben Stien then she did with the wife and the player in the beginning of the report.  The questions she presented to Ben S. seemed to be directed ‘toward’ him, while the other questions seemed to be directed ‘down’ toward the others.  <br>
<br>
One of the major problems with the American culture is that one is to blame anymore.  All of our personal problems are the result of some devious undertaking perpetrated by someone or something else.  You spill hot coffee on your lap – it’s the restaurants fault.  Your son commits suicide it’s Sony’s fault.   You fail an exam, it’s because the prof is against you – never mind the fact you spent all week partying and not studying. It’s always someone or something else’s fault… and that program is solid proof of this type of thinking.<br>
<br>
We make our own decisions, our own choices.  No one puts a gun to our heads and forces us to do anything.  The man in the beginning of the segment is making a choice to distance himself from his wife and children, and when he eventually finds himself divorced you can be assured he will tell all who will listen the story of how, “Everquest destroyed his life.”  <br>
<br>
We may all joke to each other about being addicted, but I willing to bet that for the most part, most of us can reject the temptation to log on if we have something else we wish to do.  <br>
<br>
The sad thing is, should that woman choose to sue VI/Sony there is a good chance she could win.  Certainly considering the state the law suite would be filed in, California.  The only state in the union that lets murders off for eating to many Twinkies.  <br>
<br>
There is nothing malignant about playing Everquest… it is the people who cannot set reasonable limits who cause their own dismay.  <br>
